      "Piping replacement initiated",
      "All piping in need of maintenance replaced"
    ],
    "summary": "On November 21, 2020 at 1945 hrs, a gas leak occurred on the A-Ram Powell platform in Viosca Knoll Block 956. A production operator on night crew detected gas escaping from a hole in the 6-inch Low Pressure test line. The operator activated an emergency shutdown, preventing any hydrocarbon release to the Gulf of Mexico and avoiding personnel injury. Investigation determined the root cause was pitting corrosion resulting from inadequate preventive maintenance and failure to maintain proper pipe coating.",
